arch:property.oc:show_val: All material from flotation, Sample 2 >4mm flotation, 100% sorted, recorded completely. This is the fill of a fire pit in Space 333. It is a large sample (indeed, since this was only a 20 liter sample, it is very dense), with a wide range of fragment size and moderate fragmentation. Mostly sheep-size with some large mammal. Diagnostics include sheep/goat (mostly), cattle, and equid, notably an articulated equid ankle; also one fish specimen. Ca. 15-20% burning, mostly carbonized and mostly on the smaller pieces. Considerable digestion and some gnawing. Surface condition variable but mostly fairly good although not pristine. Fairly even body part distribution for the sheep-size, but tending to the meaty parts in the non-digested. Looks like midden. Articulated equid ankle (F75-F81) sampled for carbon (DCO - 2010).
